news.title: Sales of office buildings in Europe slumped to lowest since 2009 last year
news.para: The commercial real estate market globally has endured tough trading since the COVID-19 pandemic, largely driven by higher borrowing costs and changing working patterns, the latter hitting offices particularly hard.

news.title: UK's mortgage lending rises by most since September 2022
news.para: The BoE said on Thursday that lenders approved 66,526 new mortgages for house purchase last month, higher than a median forecast of 65,400 in a Reuters poll of economists and slightly from November's upwardly revised reading.

news.title: Punjab: Struggle for land ownership rights to tenants resurfaces
news.para: As per the act one third of share was to be kept by original owners (landlords) and two thirds by tenants or cultivators and one third share works out to be 717 acres in Jeond.

news.title: McDonald’s to set up its first GCC in Hyderabad
news.para: The company has leased two floors spanning 2 lakh square feet at RMZ Nexity Tower 20 in the city. At a rental rate of around Rs 90 per square foot, the facility is set to begin operations by mid-2025.

news.title: CAQM imposes GRAP-III in Delhi-NCR and Gurugram after AQI turns ‘very poor’
news.para: Experts attributed this to poor dispersion of pollutants due to lower wind speeds. The last time Gurgaon grappled with ‘very poor' air was over a month back on Dec 27 with an AQI of 349.

news.title: District administration and civic body inspects Coimbatore metro rail project
news.para: Corporation commissioner Sivaguru Prabakaran informed that this was a primary inspection ahead of the board meeting to be convened on the Jan 31.

news.title: Dulux paints maker Akzo Nobel sees no significant market rebound in 2025
news.para: Shares in the Amsterdam-listed company dropped 4.8% by 1150 GMT, the biggest fallers on the Dutch blue chip index.

news.title: Land acquisition process begins for third and fourth phases of Noida International airport
news.para: With 15,691 landowners involved, about 37% have given their consent so far. As per the Land Acquisition Act, approval from at least 70% of the affected farmers is required to proceed with the acquisition process.

news.title: Lucknow development body gives deadline for demolition of 81 apartments
news.para: According to the notices, a demolition order was initially passed on March 31, 2009, under the Uttar Pradesh Town Planning and Development Act, 1973, after due legal process, including hearings for the concerned parties.

news.title: Real estate sector seek industry status and fiscal reforms in Budget 2025
news.para: Real estate stakeholders expect streamlined approvals, GST rationalization, sustainability incentives, rental housing policy reforms, incentives for senior living and student housing, and clarification on commercial real estate taxation from Union Budget 2025.

news.title: Jaipur development body releases GIS-based master plan 2025
news.para: Officials mentioned that with this, the public will get various types of information related to the master plan from the comfort of their homes.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to seek forest department's approval before building plan sanction
news.para: For every tree that is cut, the norm requires five trees to be planted. This is to ensure that at least one sapling survives. There have been instances in which no compensatory plantation was carried out, as well as those in which poor care led to the death of all saplings.

news.title: Govt to formulate new MHADA policy to provide affordable housing: Maharashtra deputy CM
news.para: The government will also make Mumbai slum-free, he said while addressing reporters after the lottery draw for the Pune Housing and Area Development Board (PHADB) at the Thane district collectorate.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to impose fee for transferring names on property tax records
news.para: Previously, builders sold properties before obtaining Building Use (BU) permission, and the AMC registered the buyer's name in property tax records without charging any fees.

news.title: Sebi to auction 26 properties of HBN Diaries for reserve price of Rs 83 crore in February
news.para: The order came after the Supreme Court in its order on May 14, 2024 authorised Sebi to sell the assets of HBN Dairies & Allied Ltd (HBN) with the active involvement of the liquidator.

news.title: Telangana government to set up two new IT parks near Hyderabad
news.para: Telangana IT & industries minister D Sridhar Babu also said that with industries facing challenges in acquiring land, the govt plans to come up with a dedicated land allocation policy that will allocate land based on the scale of investment and the number of jobs to be created.

news.title: Gharkul beneficiaries to get priority under PMAY: Maharashtra minister
news.para: Rural Development Minister Shri. Gore said that Prime Minister Narendra Modi is insistent that everyone in the country should get a house of their right.

news.title: Aditya Birla Housing Finance raises Rs 830 crore fund from IFC
news.para: The funds raised through IFC's investment will be utilised to address critical gaps by providing housing loans to low-income and middle-income groups, with a particular focus on encouraging homeownership among women, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Bihar RERA issues arrest warrants against three builders
news.para: The order was passed to recover an amount of about Rs 21 lakh from the builders, which is to be paid to three aggrieved home buyers, an official said.

news.title: Karnataka RERA recovers only Rs 91 crore of Rs 758.85 crore penalties from builders
news.para: According to K-RERA’s latest report, as of December 31, 2024, the authority has collected just 12% of the dues from builders, while 88% remains to be recovered.
